"v.增大，扩张；吹棒 【英】 v.增大，扩张(to make greater, more powerful) 【考】 反义词：disparage( 贬损) 【记】 ag+grand(大)+ize→ 增大 【同】 同根词：grandeur(宏 伟); grandiloquent(说大 话的) v. 增大, 扩张(范围、权势、影响、地位和名望) = augment = boost = heighten = sublime = uprear 【例】All my desired was to aggrandize my estate 我所希望的只是扩充我的家业. 【记】ag作, grand大, ize动词后缀－把蛋糕作大－扩张 【参】grandeur(n 庄严, 伟大); grandiloquent(adj 说大话的) 【反】disparage(vt 贬损); relegate(v 降级); efface(v 抹掉); undermine(v 破坏) 【记】ag + grand 盛大，大 +ize→增大 aggrandize (v.)  1630s, ""to make larger, increase,"" from French agrandiss-, present participle stem of agrandir ""to augment"" (16c.), ultimately from Latin ad ""to"" (see ad-) + grandire ""to make great,"" from grandis (see grand (adj.)). The double -g- spelling in English is by analogy with Latin words in ad-. Related: Aggrandized; aggrandizing."
